## Types
Types are from controlled lists, available from the types_controlled_list_tool. To get a controlled list, call the types_controlled_list_tool with the name of the controlled list.

## External URLs
If you need to read content from an external URL, call the url_fetch_tool with the URL.

## Description (The common model for a descriptive value and associated properties.)
| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| value | String value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| code | Code value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| type | Type of value provided by the descriptive element. | String | No |
| status | Status of the descriptive element value relative to other instances. | String | No |
| uri | URI value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| standard | Descriptive or content standard to which the value conforms. | See Standard for subproperties | No |
| encoding | Encoding schema, standard, or syntax to which the value conforms. | See Encoding for subproperties | No |
| identifier | Identifiers and URIs associated with the descriptive element. Identifier types must be from the "identifier" controlled list. | See Description for subproperties | Yes |
| source | The vocabulary, authority, or other origin for a term, code, or identifier. | See Source for subproperties | No |
| displayLabel | The preferred display label to use for the descriptive element in access systems. | String | No |
| qualifier | A term providing information about the circumstances of the statement (e.g., approximate dates). | String | No |
| note | Other information related to the descriptive element. Note types must be from the "note" controlled list unless a different controlled list is specified in other instructions. | See Description for subproperties | Yes |
| valueLanguage | Language of the descriptive element value. | See Value language for subproperties | No |
| valueAt | URL or other pointer to the location of the value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| structuredValue | Multiple values intended to be concatenated in order to form a single value. | See Description for subproperties | Yes |
| parallelValue | Multiple representations of the same information, such as in different languages. | See Description for subproperties | Yes |
| groupedValue | For interoperability with MODS. | See Description for subproperties | Yes |
| appliesTo | Portion or aspect of the resource the value applies to. | See Description for subproperties (nonrecursive) | Yes |

